- The same way you feel about Botox:

247
00:14:59.690 --> 00:15:01.440
Painful and unnecessary.

248
00:15:01.940 --> 00:15:06.690
- Seventy-four, 75, 76. Seventy-six guests.
- Seventy-five sounds better.

249
00:15:06.860 --> 00:15:10.360
A small wedding of 75 guests.

250
00:15:10.530 --> 00:15:13.620
Seventy-six trombones, yes.
Seventy-six guests, no.

251
00:15:13.790 --> 00:15:15.790
As a wedding gift,
Charlotte had given me...

252
00:15:15.950 --> 00:15:18.580
...Anthony Marantino,
friend and wedding planner.

253
00:15:18.750 --> 00:15:20.370
All right.

254
00:15:20.880 --> 00:15:22.710
Well, that's...

255
00:15:23.170 --> 00:15:25.880
Cutthroat. I love it.
I hope you're this decisive...

256
00:15:26.050 --> 00:15:28.970
...when it comes to location and the dress.
- I found the dress.

257
00:15:29.130 --> 00:15:31.550
- What? When?
- Yeah, the other day. I have it.

258
00:15:33.760 --> 00:15:37.230
- This is gonna be good.
- I am so excited.

259
00:15:37.390 --> 00:15:39.230
Okay.

260
00:15:39.730 --> 00:15:41.600
Here it is.

261
00:15:46.150 --> 00:15:48.400
That was the exact reaction
I was aiming for.

262
00:15:48.740 --> 00:15:52.070
It's pretty, but it's... It's so simple.

263
00:15:52.240 --> 00:15:54.120
It's simple and classic.

264
00:15:54.280 --> 00:15:59.410
When I saw it, I thought'
"That is what I should marry Big in."

265
00:15:59.580 --> 00:16:03.880
- Well, who's it by? What's the label?
- No one. I found it at a vintage shop.

266
00:16:04.960 --> 00:16:07.590
The bride wore a dress by no one.

267
00:16:07.760 --> 00:16:10.340
Oh, come on,
you know I'm gonna merchandise it up...

268
00:16:10.510 --> 00:16:12.930
...style it up with some shoes.
Right.

269
00:16:14.140 --> 00:16:16.100
The invitation is fancier than the dress.

270
00:16:16.270 --> 00:16:18.220
- I heard that.
- I meant you to.

271
00:16:18.770 --> 00:16:20.810
Don't tell anyone.

272
00:16:30.110 --> 00:16:33.870
"The ultimate single gal, Carrie
Bradshaw, will be married in Manolos...

273
00:16:34.030 --> 00:16:38.620
...to New York financier
John James Preston come fall."

274
00:16:38.790 --> 00:16:41.960
- Our wedding's on Page Six.
- Who would put that in there?

275
00:16:42.120 --> 00:16:47.420
"Proving to single gals everywhere
that there can be a happy ending over 40."

276
00:16:49.840 --> 00:16:51.340
- Carrie.
- Congratulations.

277
00:16:51.510 --> 00:16:55.010
It seemed everywhere I went,
people had seen Page Six.

278
00:16:55.180 --> 00:16:59.140
Even people you didn't expect,
like my Vogue editor, Enid.

279
00:16:59.310 --> 00:17:01.890
We're putting together
our annual age issue...

280
00:17:02.060 --> 00:17:03.560
...and we'd like you to do 40.

281
00:17:03.730 --> 00:17:05.980
- Great. Who am I interviewing?
- No.

282
00:17:06.150 --> 00:17:08.270
You. You are 40.

283
00:17:08.440 --> 00:17:12.150
I want you to be featured in the magazine
as the 40-year-old...

284
00:17:12.320 --> 00:17:14.990
And here's the brilliant twist.
- Bride.

285
00:17:16.990 --> 00:17:20.290
Wait, I'm... I would be in the magazine?

286
00:17:20.450 --> 00:17:23.920
In bridal couture.
It's a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity...

287
00:17:24.080 --> 00:17:29.210
...so spare me a week of
faux soul-searching and just say yes.

288
00:17:29.380 --> 00:17:32.800
Enid, I am so very flattered,
but honestly, I...

289
00:17:32.970 --> 00:17:34.680
Carrie, Vogue designers.

290
00:17:34.840 --> 00:17:36.510
Vogue photographers.

291
00:17:36.680 --> 00:17:38.350
Vogue airbrushing.

292
00:17:38.970 --> 00:17:41.850
Nod your head. Yes.

293
00:17:44.850 --> 00:17:47.020
Thank you. It will be a sensation.

294
00:17:47.190 --> 00:17:49.650
We're calling it "The Last Single Girl."

295
00:17:49.820 --> 00:17:53.860
Well, I'm hardly the last single girl.

296
00:17:54.030 --> 00:17:58.200
No, but 40 is the last age a woman
can be photographed in a wedding gown...

297
00:17:58.370 --> 00:18:01.290
...without the unintended
Diane Arbus subtext.

298
00:18:01.450 --> 00:18:04.960
I thought the issue was
"Great Style at Every Age."

299
00:18:05.120 --> 00:18:08.210
Style, yes. Bride, no.

300
00:18:13.050 --> 00:18:15.220
- Is that better?
- Just your typical Wednesday.

301
00:18:15.380 --> 00:18:17.890
Hanging out with old friends
like Stanford Blatch...

302
00:18:18.510 --> 00:18:21.390
...and new friends like Vera Wang.

303
00:18:21.560 --> 00:18:25.180
She's looking at home for someone
who didn't think she had the bride gene.

304
00:18:25.350 --> 00:18:28.060
- Well, I guess with the right man...
- And the right dress.

305
00:18:28.610 --> 00:18:32.070
When I get married, I'm wearing
something like that, only bigger.

306
00:18:33.360 --> 00:18:34.860
Beauty. Hot.

307
00:18:35.400 --> 00:18:36.900
Love the veil.

308
00:18:37.070 --> 00:18:39.410
And Carolina Herrera.

309
00:18:42.040 --> 00:18:44.410
Nothing fancy, but it's beautiful.
Good work.

310
00:18:44.580 --> 00:18:45.710
Great, let's do it.

311
00:18:56.930 --> 00:18:59.090
And Christian Lacroix.

312
00:19:08.600 --> 00:19:09.900
And Lanvin.

313
00:19:14.860 --> 00:19:15.900
And Dior.

314
00:19:24.620 --> 00:19:27.200
And Oscar de la Renta.

315
00:19:31.130 --> 00:19:35.420
And finally, Vivienne Westwood.

316
00:19:35.590 --> 00:19:37.920
A dress so special...

317
00:19:38.090 --> 00:19:43.100
...it could bring a wedding tear from
even the most unbelieving of women.

318
00:19:49.230 --> 00:19:53.480
And then, the impossible happened.

319
00:20:19.760 --> 00:20:21.130
And just like that...

320
00:20:21.300 --> 00:20:25.350
...Vivienne Westwood
kicked my sweet little suit's ass.

321
00:20:34.440 --> 00:20:36.150
Can I lean?

322
00:20:43.200 --> 00:20:46.330
Are you the last person in New York
still taking out library books?

323
00:20:46.490 --> 00:20:48.790
I love the smell.

324
00:20:52.710 --> 00:20:55.670
Oh. That's an oldie.

325
00:20:56.130 --> 00:20:58.550
"Love Letters of Great Men,
Volume One."

326
00:20:58.710 --> 00:21:00.800
- Oh, am I in there?
- No, no.

327
00:21:00.970 --> 00:21:05.090
But some of your classmates are'
like Voltaire, Napoleon.

328
00:21:06.180 --> 00:21:10.350
- Young lady, you need to get glasses.
- No, I don't. I have yours.

329
00:21:10.520 --> 00:21:12.730
Okay, here's Napoleon.

330
00:21:13.190 --> 00:21:16.860
"My dearest Josephine,
I wake consumed with thoughts of you."

331
00:21:17.020 --> 00:21:20.230
Typical short guy.
Gives it all away upfront.

332
00:21:20.570 --> 00:21:23.530
- Why are you reading this?
- It's research for my new book.

333
00:21:23.700 --> 00:21:27.280
- Oh. What's it about?
- Love.

334
00:21:27.450 --> 00:21:29.080
I used to write about finding love.

335
00:21:29.240 --> 00:21:32.660
Now I wanna write about
what happens after you've found it.

336
00:21:32.830 --> 00:21:34.580
Interesting.

337
00:21:34.750 --> 00:21:38.000
- What happens?
- Mm. Stay tuned.

338
00:21:38.670 --> 00:21:40.920
Oh, here, listen. It's Beethoven.

339
00:21:41.090 --> 00:21:43.470
Bring it, Ludwig.

340
00:21:45.090 --> 00:21:48.600
"My thoughts go out to you'
my immortal beloved.

341
00:21:48.760 --> 00:21:52.560
I can live only wholly with you
or not at all."

342
00:21:52.730 --> 00:21:54.060
Good stuff.

343
00:21:54.230 --> 00:21:56.600
"Be calm my life, my all.

344
00:21:56.770 --> 00:21:59.610
Only by calm consideration
of our existence...

345
00:21:59.780 --> 00:22:02.570
...can we achieve
our purpose to live together.

346
00:22:02.740 --> 00:22:05.150
Oh, continue to love me.
Never misjudge...

347
00:22:05.320 --> 00:22:08.280
...the most faithful heart of your beloved.

348
00:22:08.450 --> 00:22:13.580
Ever thine. Ever mine. Ever ours."

349
00:22:17.500 --> 00:22:19.920
Have you ever written me a love letter?

350
00:22:20.090 --> 00:22:21.550
Does a love fax count?

351
00:22:22.460 --> 00:22:26.590
- When have I ever gotten a love fax?
- Oh, I'm sure my secretary sent you one...

352
00:22:26.760 --> 00:22:29.100
...at some point.
- Yeah.

353
00:22:29.560 --> 00:22:32.640
What can I tell you, baby?
It's not my style.

354
00:22:32.810 --> 00:22:36.190
Besides, those guys had to write.
They were separated from their loves...

355
00:22:36.350 --> 00:22:40.020
...by wars
and hundreds and hundreds of miles.

356
00:22:40.190 --> 00:22:42.320
I'm right here.

357
00:22:42.480 --> 00:22:44.440
Hello.

358
00:22:45.900 --> 00:22:49.990
- You make me very happy.
- Yeah, yeah. Put it in writing.

359
00:22:51.160 --> 00:22:55.830
With my mind prenuptially preoccupied,
I became delinquent with my library books.

360
00:22:56.000 --> 00:22:59.790
So now the tragic love stories
ofWuthering Heights and Love Story...

361
00:22:59.960 --> 00:23:02.090
...were going to cost me
more than a few tears.

362
00:23:02.250 --> 00:23:04.260
Excuse me, which way is the wedding?

363
00:23:04.510 --> 00:23:06.380
Up the stairs.

364
00:23:17.350 --> 00:23:19.480
It was perfect.

365
00:23:19.650 --> 00:23:22.690
Big and I would be married
in the classic New York landmark...

366
00:23:22.860 --> 00:23:26.610
...that housed all the great love stories.

367
00:23:29.780 --> 00:23:31.570
Where is the waiter with the check?

368
00:23:31.740 --> 00:23:35.370
Jeez, Miranda, relax.
Magda hasn't even finished yet.

369
00:23:35.540 --> 00:23:38.160
I still have a brief to work on
when I get home.

370
00:23:38.330 --> 00:23:41.880
- I have to go to the bathroom.
- I'll take him.

371
00:23:42.040 --> 00:23:43.130
Thank you, Magda.

372
00:23:44.050 --> 00:23:47.840
We're gonna wash that beautiful face.
Come, darling.

373
00:23:50.220 --> 00:23:51.220
What?

374
00:23:51.390 --> 00:23:53.890
We can't let the hard-working nanny
finish her supper?

375
00:23:54.060 --> 00:23:57.680
I'm sorry, I'm exhausted.
Brady woke me up at 5 a.m.

376
00:23:57.850 --> 00:24:00.900
- Hey, he woke me up too.
- Yeah.

377
00:24:01.060 --> 00:24:03.860
We gotta stop letting Brady
come into our bed.

378
00:24:08.240 --> 00:24:10.070
You got milk on your top lip.

379
00:24:11.870 --> 00:24:13.030
What now?

380
00:24:13.200 --> 00:24:16.490
- It's like you're always criticizing me.
- I am not.

381
00:24:17.410 --> 00:24:21.580
You wanna go through life with foam
on your lip and no one ever telling you?

382
00:24:29.220 --> 00:24:31.430
Anything you wanna tell me?

383
00:24:38.520 --> 00:24:41.390
Hm. Is there anything you wanna tell me?

384
00:24:48.030 --> 00:24:52.530
- Yeah. Yeah.
- Wait. Wait. Don't come already.

385
00:24:52.700 --> 00:24:56.280
- Yeah.
- No, wait. Get on top.

386
00:24:56.450 --> 00:24:59.080
Let's just get it over with.

387
00:25:03.290 --> 00:25:06.710
I mean, we gotta get up
in four and a half hours.

388
00:25:07.920 --> 00:25:11.380
We never have sex
and you wanna get it over with?

389
00:25:16.600 --> 00:25:20.470
- Steve, we have sex.
- When was the last time we had sex?

390
00:25:21.440 --> 00:25:23.230
Um...

391
00:25:25.980 --> 00:25:28.820
There was snow on the ground.

392
00:25:35.320 --> 00:25:37.990
- How often do you guys have sex?
- Sex.

393
00:25:38.160 --> 00:25:39.990
- Miranda, please.
What?

394
00:25:40.450 --> 00:25:42.580
She's 3.
She doesn't know what it means.

395
00:25:42.750 --> 00:25:44.750
I'm 41 and I still don't know
what it means.

396
00:25:44.920 --> 00:25:47.170
I know, but she is repeating everything.

397
00:25:47.340 --> 00:25:51.510
If I'd known the girl talk was gonna be on
lockdown, I wouldn't have flown 3000 miles.

398
00:25:51.670 --> 00:25:54.300
No, we can talk.
Let's just not use that word.

399
00:25:54.930 --> 00:25:58.470
Fine. How often do you guys...?

400
00:25:58.640 --> 00:26:00.350
- Color?
Thank you.

401
00:26:00.520 --> 00:26:04.850
Well, I can't color enough.
I could color all day every day.

402
00:26:05.020 --> 00:26:09.110
If I had my way,
I would use every crayon in my box.

403
00:26:09.270 --> 00:26:12.530
We get it. You love to color.

404
00:26:12.690 --> 00:26:14.450
Why are you asking?

405
00:26:14.610 --> 00:26:19.830
Well, last night Steve and I were coloring,
and I was just about to...

406
00:26:19.990 --> 00:26:22.750
Come.
I'm sorry, there's no crayon equivalent.

407
00:26:22.910 --> 00:26:26.460
And he wanted to switch positions
and I said:

408
00:26:27.460 --> 00:26:29.040
"Let's just get it over with."

409
00:26:31.630 --> 00:26:34.220
- He kept trying to make it last longer.
- This is bad?

410
00:26:34.380 --> 00:26:37.220
- It is when you have a full-time job.
- I have a full-time job.

411
00:26:37.390 --> 00:26:40.220
You don't also have a 5-year-old,
play dates, PTA meetings...

412
00:26:40.390 --> 00:26:43.850
...and a mother-in-law in a rest home
with advancing Alzheimer's.

413
00:26:44.020 --> 00:26:47.230
We're just going through
a no-coloring phase.

414
00:26:47.400 --> 00:26:50.190
- It comes and goes, right?
Every couple is different.

415
00:26:50.570 --> 00:26:53.070
Harry and I make love
two, three times a week.

416
00:26:53.240 --> 00:26:56.490
- Great, now I feel worse.
- Well, when was the last time for you?

417
00:26:58.490 --> 00:27:00.570
- Six months ago.
- Oh, my.

418
00:27:01.870 --> 00:27:03.870
It sounds long.

419
00:27:04.040 --> 00:27:07.000
- But... But that's a dry spell.
- I bet it is.

420
00:27:07.170 --> 00:27:10.580
Hey, Carrie. What about you and Big?

421
00:27:11.040 --> 00:27:14.090
Come on. I told. Tell.

422
00:27:15.630 --> 00:27:17.590
But I will tell you this.

423
00:27:17.760 --> 00:27:19.550
When Big colors...

424
00:27:21.100 --> 00:27:24.520
...he rarely stays inside the lines.

425
00:27:24.680 --> 00:27:27.180
Well, this has been very helpful.

426
00:27:36.950 --> 00:27:38.780
John?

427
00:27:45.620 --> 00:27:47.830
- Hey.
- Come here.

428
00:27:56.010 --> 00:27:58.800
Totally outside the lines.

429
00:28:06.770 --> 00:28:10.140
Well, send it to Smith Jerrod
at the office address.

430
00:28:10.600 --> 00:28:12.940
I gotta go. Something just came up.

431
00:28:15.030 --> 00:28:18.940
- I got a gift for you.
- So far, I like it.

432
00:28:27.410 --> 00:28:28.750
How'd...?

433
00:28:29.330 --> 00:28:32.460
Wait. That was you on the phone
at the auction.

434
00:28:32.630 --> 00:28:36.750
- I knew how much you wanted it.
- But I was gonna buy it for myself.

435
00:28:37.170 --> 00:28:39.010
Well, I wanted to give it to you.

436
00:28:39.840 --> 00:28:42.010
For our anniversary.

437
00:28:42.180 --> 00:28:44.180
We met five years ago today.

438
00:28:45.680 --> 00:28:47.010
Right.

439
00:28:48.100 --> 00:28:49.430
Do you like it?

440
00:28:49.600 --> 00:28:52.520
Well, just to be clear,
this is a ring with diamonds...

441
00:28:52.690 --> 00:28:55.440
...it's not a diamond ring, right?
- Yeah.

442
00:28:56.690 --> 00:28:58.730
Well, in that case, I love it.

443
00:28:58.900 --> 00:29:02.280
It's my second favorite thing
I've ever found in there.

444
00:29:04.030 --> 00:29:08.700
Now, my gift is a little bit more oral.

445
00:29:10.120 --> 00:29:15.040
- Babe, I have to go to bed.
- Bed? It's 7:30.

446
00:29:15.210 --> 00:29:18.880
I have to be at the studio by 6 a.m.
And I need to get a workout in before that.

447
00:29:19.050 --> 00:29:20.710
You see, this is how it starts.

448
00:29:20.880 --> 00:29:25.220
Next thing you know, we're only
having sex three or four times a week.

449
00:29:55.250 --> 00:29:59.210
And that is how Samantha learned
she had a new neighbor.

450
00:30:00.090 --> 00:30:03.010
From then on, night after night...

451
00:30:03.180 --> 00:30:05.760
...while Smith got his beauty sleep...

452
00:30:07.680 --> 00:30:12.430
...Samantha found something
more interesting to watch than TiVo.

453
00:30:16.610 --> 00:30:19.440
- Keep going.
- Okay.

454
00:30:20.480 --> 00:30:22.610
- Keep them closed.
- Okay.

455
00:30:24.110 --> 00:30:27.450
Okay. Open them.

456
00:30:29.780 --> 00:30:31.790
Double doors.

457
00:30:31.950 --> 00:30:34.410
So far, so good.

458
00:30:44.800 --> 00:30:46.930
Oh, my God.

459
00:30:50.180 --> 00:30:54.930
- Oh, you did me proud, mister.
- You like it?

460
00:30:56.310 --> 00:30:57.390
"Like it?"

461
00:31:02.230 --> 00:31:04.400
It's love at first sight.

462
00:31:04.570 --> 00:31:06.780
Oh, my.

463
00:31:06.950 --> 00:31:10.160
Here. Wait.

464
00:31:10.330 --> 00:31:11.870
Hold this.

465
00:31:19.630 --> 00:31:22.500
Now I believe this is all really happening.

466
00:31:23.420 --> 00:31:25.510
I can't believe it sold so fast.

467
00:31:25.670 --> 00:31:28.550
- It's a sign.
- Yeah, it's a sign I priced it too low.

468
00:31:29.970 --> 00:31:33.350
Hey, that's the food. Will you buzz
them in? And money's on the table.

469
00:31:33.520 --> 00:31:36.850
I'm gonna get started on the closet.
I should be done in about 17 years.

470
00:31:37.020 --> 00:31:40.310
All right. Pink Post-it: Take.

471
00:31:40.690 --> 00:31:43.770
Purple: Toss. Yellow: Storage.

472
00:31:43.940 --> 00:31:46.360
Oh, you're very good friends.

473
00:31:52.280 --> 00:31:54.080
Oh, my God.

474
00:31:56.540 --> 00:31:59.870
I can't believe it.
Lily, look who it is. Aunt Samantha.

475
00:32:02.290 --> 00:32:05.880
- What are you doing here?
- A lot of shit went down in this place.

476
00:32:06.050 --> 00:32:08.590
Attention must be paid.

477
00:32:12.350 --> 00:32:14.890
Really, champagne.

478
00:32:21.980 --> 00:32:23.900
- Remember this?
- Oh, yeah.

479
00:32:24.070 --> 00:32:27.360
While Samantha put on
The Best of the '80s...

480
00:32:28.780 --> 00:32:31.700
...I put on the worst.

481
00:32:38.870 --> 00:32:40.500
Banana clip.

482
00:32:44.250 --> 00:32:46.050
Yeah.

483
00:32:46.590 --> 00:32:48.260
Work it.

484
00:32:50.470 --> 00:32:52.010
Madonna.

485
00:32:52.180 --> 00:32:55.390
Whoo, whoo!

486
00:33:04.400 --> 00:33:05.440
No fun.

487
00:33:23.830 --> 00:33:26.580
It took four friends three days...

488
00:33:26.740 --> 00:33:30.830
...to put 20 years into 38 boxes.

489
00:33:53.750 --> 00:33:55.870
