- No! No!

747
00:53:02.190 --> 00:53:03.900
Come on, we're gonna get in the car.

748
00:53:04.810 --> 00:53:07.150
It's all right, it's all right.

749
00:53:28.960 --> 00:53:30.510
Let's go, man. Move it.

750
00:53:59.450 --> 00:54:02.450
I thought I would still be in extreme pain.

751
00:54:05.670 --> 00:54:07.630
I feel nothing.

752
00:54:10.420 --> 00:54:12.760
I'd like some more nothing.

753
00:54:18.720 --> 00:54:20.430
Yes, I'm still jilted.

754
00:54:22.390 --> 00:54:25.810
What the hell got into him?
He was perfectly fine at the dinner.

755
00:54:26.860 --> 00:54:29.360
I knew it when he called last night.

756
00:54:29.900 --> 00:54:32.820
- I could tell.
- Then why didn't you say anything?

757
00:54:34.900 --> 00:54:37.740
I didn't wanna believe it. I di...

758
00:54:37.910 --> 00:54:41.160
I didn't even wanna say it out loud.

759
00:54:43.660 --> 00:54:46.790
- Now I have nowhere to live.
- You'll stay here.

760
00:54:46.960 --> 00:54:48.210
Forever.

761
00:54:49.340 --> 00:54:51.840
Maybe you should eat something.

762
00:54:53.010 --> 00:54:55.340
- Anyone? Hungry?
- No.

763
00:54:57.220 --> 00:55:00.390
I can never go back there again.
How am I gonna get my clothes?

764
00:55:00.560 --> 00:55:04.730
Oh, honey, I can hire people to do all that.
Anything you need.

765
00:55:05.480 --> 00:55:06.690
A hit man?

766
00:55:08.690 --> 00:55:11.520
I have nothing to wear
but a wedding gown.

767
00:55:12.320 --> 00:55:14.990
You have your honeymoon clothes here.

768
00:55:16.150 --> 00:55:18.490
Well, there's the silver lining.

769
00:55:20.370 --> 00:55:24.540
A honeymoon
at a romantic Mexican resort...

770
00:55:24.700 --> 00:55:26.620
...that's prepaid on my credit card...

771
00:55:26.790 --> 00:55:29.250
...because I wanted to surprise
the man who jilted me.

772
00:55:29.420 --> 00:55:31.080
I can get you out of that.

773
00:55:31.250 --> 00:55:34.170
Worse comes to worse'
I'll say there was a death or something.

774
00:55:34.340 --> 00:55:36.050
Wasn't there?

775
00:55:39.720 --> 00:55:43.220
Keep those eyes closed.
Keep them closed.

776
00:55:57.700 --> 00:55:58.820
Charlotte.

777
00:55:58.990 --> 00:56:00.780
Come here. Come here.

778
00:56:03.830 --> 00:56:06.620
I did something really bad, I think.

779
00:56:07.330 --> 00:56:10.170
I said something to Big
at the rehearsal dinner.

780
00:56:11.710 --> 00:56:12.880
What do you mean?

781
00:56:13.040 --> 00:56:16.550
It was right after Steve showed up.
I was upset.

782
00:56:16.710 --> 00:56:20.430
Big came over to me'
and I said something like:

783
00:56:21.260 --> 00:56:23.350
"You're crazy to get married."

784
00:56:24.140 --> 00:56:26.060
It just came out.

785
00:56:26.220 --> 00:56:30.190
- Do you think it's totally the reason?
- No.

786
00:56:30.350 --> 00:56:33.360
Big has been weird
about marriage for years.

787
00:56:35.530 --> 00:56:39.030
- I keep thinking I should tell Carrie.
- No, No, no.

788
00:56:39.200 --> 00:56:42.490
This is a bad time to even mention it.

789
00:56:43.580 --> 00:56:48.290
No, no, no. Find another time later.

790
00:56:48.450 --> 00:56:49.450
Uh-huh.

791
00:56:49.620 --> 00:56:53.580
Well, it turns out, I couldn't get her
out of the honeymoon, but I got us in.

792
00:56:54.170 --> 00:56:57.460
- What?
- I just booked us three seats on the flight.

793
00:56:57.630 --> 00:57:00.340
Mexico, here we come.

794
00:57:00.720 --> 00:57:03.550
