810
00:58:48.350 --> 00:58:52.440
Here. No more honeymoon stuff.
This is very important.

811
00:58:58.780 --> 00:59:00.530
Here she comes.

812
00:59:13.790 --> 00:59:15.550
It's going to be a gorgeous sunset.

813
00:59:17.760 --> 00:59:19.010
Close the shutters.

814
00:59:26.180 --> 00:59:27.470
All of them.

815
00:59:48.660 --> 00:59:50.290
Morning.

816
00:59:52.670 --> 00:59:54.170
Did I dream it?

817
01:00:08.100 --> 01:00:09.890
Carrie?

818
01:00:10.850 --> 01:00:13.480
It's dinnertime. You slept the whole day.

819
01:00:14.610 --> 01:00:16.230
So?

820
01:00:29.240 --> 01:00:33.710
Honey? You have to eat a little breakfast.

821
01:00:35.710 --> 01:00:36.880
I'm tired.

822
01:00:37.040 --> 01:00:40.500
Well, eat something,
then you can go back to sleep.

823
01:01:15.120 --> 01:01:17.460
- Oh, thank you, Paulo.
- Sure.

824
01:01:20.670 --> 01:01:25.550
With all this gorgeous fresh food, you're
gonna eat that pudding crap the entire trip?

825
01:01:25.720 --> 01:01:28.260
It's the only thing in the pantry
that's totally safe.

826
01:01:28.430 --> 01:01:32.220
See? "Made in Poughkeepsie."
I didn't wanna chance it.

827
01:01:32.390 --> 01:01:34.140
It's a five-star resort.

828
01:01:34.520 --> 01:01:36.520
It's Mexico.

829
01:01:44.990 --> 01:01:46.240
Carrie.

830
01:01:48.820 --> 01:01:49.950
Is there coffee?

831
01:01:50.990 --> 01:01:53.740
Yeah. Yeah, of course.

832
01:02:00.840 --> 01:02:03.250
The sun feels nice.

833
01:02:07.090 --> 01:02:09.220
Jesus, honey, wax much?

834
01:02:09.590 --> 01:02:12.560
What? I didn't know
I was gonna be wearing a bathing suit.

835
01:02:12.930 --> 01:02:15.680
- What are you talking about?
- I forgot to wax.

836
01:02:15.850 --> 01:02:19.650
- Since when, 1998?
I've had other things on my mind.

837
01:02:19.810 --> 01:02:22.400
I could be on death row
and not have that situation.

838
01:02:22.570 --> 01:02:25.650
Well, when you're married,
you have a different set of priorities.

839
01:02:25.820 --> 01:02:27.450
Oh, honey, don't blame marriage.

840
01:02:27.610 --> 01:02:30.490
This one's married and
she's not growing a national forest.

841
01:02:30.660 --> 01:02:34.540
How do you even cross your legs?
Let me make you a spa appointment.

842
01:02:34.700 --> 01:02:37.330
Any thicker,
and you won't be able to find it.

843
01:02:39.670 --> 01:02:41.630
So, what, it's my fault?

844
01:02:41.790 --> 01:02:44.920
I let the sex go out of my marriage.
I deserve what I got?

845
01:02:45.090 --> 01:02:48.800
- Thanks for understanding.
- Honey, I'm sorry. That's not what I...

846
01:02:48.970 --> 01:02:50.590
I'm fine.

847
01:03:01.900 --> 01:03:04.520
Hey, let's go down to the hotel
for dinner tonight.

848
01:03:04.690 --> 01:03:06.480
- Really?
- Yeah.

849
01:03:06.650 --> 01:03:09.360
I gotta do something
to pull me out of my "Mexi-coma."

850
01:03:09.530 --> 01:03:12.110
Oh, honey, you made a little joke.

851
01:03:12.280 --> 01:03:14.200
Good for you.

852
01:03:15.040 --> 01:03:16.200
Yeah.

853
01:03:32.550 --> 01:03:36.720
- My name is Felix, I'll be your server.
- Felix, we'll start with cuatro margaritas.

854
01:03:36.890 --> 01:03:39.100
Oh, No, I'm not drinking.
Just bottled water.

855
01:03:39.270 --> 01:03:41.520
- I'll drink hers.
- May I have your room numbers?

856
01:03:42.940 --> 01:03:46.900
We're staying in one of the private houses.
Uh, number 3.

857
01:03:47.480 --> 01:03:48.650
Very good, Mrs. Preston.

858
01:03:53.490 --> 01:03:55.160
That was like taking a bullet.

859
01:04:00.410 --> 01:04:03.170
Charlotte has pudding in her Prada.

860
01:04:09.510 --> 01:04:11.970
- Will I ever laugh again?
- Yes.

861
01:04:12.130 --> 01:04:15.850
- When?
- When something is really, really funny.

862
01:04:18.810 --> 01:04:22.600
Thank God for that mariachi band
or I'd be able to hear my own thoughts.

863
01:04:24.150 --> 01:04:26.560
Fabulous. And keep them coming.

864
01:04:28.190 --> 01:04:29.570
Thanks.

865
01:04:35.280 --> 01:04:36.740
Thank you.

866
01:04:42.790 --> 01:04:45.500
He couldn't get out of the car.

867
01:04:45.960 --> 01:04:49.420
After 10 years
of what he already put me through...

868
01:04:49.590 --> 01:04:53.760
...he couldn't make the effort
and get out of the car.

869
01:04:54.050 --> 01:04:55.890
I made the effort.

870
01:04:56.050 --> 01:04:57.850
I put a bird on my head.

871
01:04:58.010 --> 01:04:59.560
- Is that what that was?
- Yeah.

872
01:04:59.720 --> 01:05:02.270
- I thought it was feathers.
- It was a bird.

873
01:05:02.430 --> 01:05:05.770
- It was beautiful.
Beautiful.

874
01:05:06.150 --> 01:05:08.310
He's a bad guy.

875
01:05:09.360 --> 01:05:11.570
Always was.

876
01:05:11.740 --> 01:05:15.650
- Bad guys do bad things.
- And good guys do bad things.

877
01:05:15.820 --> 01:05:18.740
The good guys screw you
and the bad guys screw you.

878
01:05:18.910 --> 01:05:20.990
The rest of them
don't know how to screw you.

879
01:05:21.160 --> 01:05:24.290
- Trust me, I've done the legwork.
After everything I know...

880
01:05:24.460 --> 01:05:28.830
...after 20 years of
everything we've learned...

881
01:05:29.000 --> 01:05:32.920
...I threw it all away for the thrill of
putting his name on the honeymoon suite.

882
01:05:34.380 --> 01:05:36.680
If I met me now, I wouldn't know me.

883
01:05:38.140 --> 01:05:40.600
As long as we're going down this road...

884
01:05:40.760 --> 01:05:45.230
...I can't believe
that my life revolves around a man.

885
01:05:45.390 --> 01:05:47.730
On what planet
did I allow that to happen?

886
01:05:47.900 --> 01:05:48.980
But you love him.

887
01:05:49.150 --> 01:05:52.860
Does that mean saying his name
50 times more a day than I say my own?

888
01:05:53.570 --> 01:05:57.400
Does it mean worrying about him
and his needs before me and mine?

889
01:05:57.570 --> 01:05:59.950
Is it all about the other person?
Is that love?

890
01:06:00.120 --> 01:06:03.490
- No, that's marriage.
- Even this ring.

891
01:06:03.660 --> 01:06:05.160
I wanted to buy this for myself.

892
01:06:05.330 --> 01:06:07.580
That meant something to me'
to be able to do that.

893
01:06:07.750 --> 01:06:11.380
- And then he buys it for me.
- Because he knew how much you loved it.

894
01:06:11.540 --> 01:06:15.460
Yes, but now every time I look down at it,
I see him not me.

895
01:06:17.800 --> 01:06:20.340
- Is every...?
- We'll take another round.

896
01:06:20.640 --> 01:06:23.680
- Another?
- Relax. We're on vacation.

897
01:06:23.850 --> 01:06:25.600
Technically, we're on my honeymoon.

898
01:06:25.770 --> 01:06:28.690
No, I think we're on their honeymoon.

899
01:06:30.230 --> 01:06:32.610
Yeah, it's all so hot three days in.

900
01:06:40.160 --> 01:06:43.660
"Mailbox full." Yea, I'll bet it is.

901
01:06:43.830 --> 01:06:46.120
- There's no time like the present.
No.

902
01:06:47.040 --> 01:06:48.870
I'm not ready to face it all yet.

903
01:06:49.580 --> 01:06:52.840
Hey. I'm going for a run
and then to the gym for Pilates.

904
01:06:53.000 --> 01:06:55.050
Anybody wanna...?

905
01:06:56.300 --> 01:06:58.590
- Hi.
- Hey, good news.

906
01:06:58.760 --> 01:07:00.800
I got an e-mail
from your buyer's attorney.

907
01:07:00.970 --> 01:07:04.600
Thy, re willing to sell you back
your old apartment at the escalated price...

908
01:07:04.760 --> 01:07:07.600
...and "are willing to vacate
by the time you return...

909
01:07:07.770 --> 01:07:09.810
...pending an additional financial offer."

910
01:07:09.980 --> 01:07:13.650
Well, apparently you can go home again,
but it'll cost you.

911
01:07:13.820 --> 01:07:16.530
- Let's work on getting your things there.
Wow...

912
01:07:16.940 --> 01:07:19.610
...you two could rule the world.

913
01:07:20.280 --> 01:07:22.820
After her workout,
Charlotte couldn't help but think...

914
01:07:22.990 --> 01:07:24.910
...how truly blessed she was.

915
01:07:25.080 --> 01:07:28.790
This week had made her feel more grateful
than ever for her happy marriage.

916
01:07:28.960 --> 01:07:33.290
And just for a second, while picturing
her loved ones at home in New York...

917
01:07:33.460 --> 01:07:37.630
...she forgot where she was
and opened her mouth.

918
01:08:00.030 --> 01:08:01.070
Hello, miss.

919
01:08:05.240 --> 01:08:07.450
- Have you had that happen?
Not recently.

920
01:08:07.620 --> 01:08:09.330
Sweetie, what's...?

921
01:08:09.500 --> 01:08:11.410
It's locked, she's mopping.

922
01:08:11.580 --> 01:08:13.170
Try the...

923
01:08:22.050 --> 01:08:24.470
- Did you just...?
- Shut up, shut up, shut up!

924
01:08:24.640 --> 01:08:26.640
And just like that...

925
01:08:26.810 --> 01:08:28.850
...Charlotte "Poughkeepsied"
in her pants.

926
01:08:31.060 --> 01:08:34.600
Oh, my God.

927
01:08:38.110 --> 01:08:39.440
Miranda was right.

928
01:08:39.610 --> 01:08:44.490
When something was really,
really funny, I laughed.

929
01:08:45.530 --> 01:08:47.450
Oh, my God.

930
01:09:12.230 --> 01:09:13.600
First message:

931
01:09:13.770 --> 01:09:18.900
Received Saturday,
September 20th, 12:30 p.m.

932
01:09:19.070 --> 01:09:22.480
Carrie, call me.
I need to talk to you before...

933
01:10:14.500 --> 01:10:18.370
There was no better time I could think of
to hire an assistant.

934
01:10:18.540 --> 01:10:22.000
Um, no. I do not lift boxes.

935
01:10:23.000 --> 01:10:27.260
Yeah, definitely, no.
I would love a career in fashion.

936
01:10:27.430 --> 01:10:29.380
Oh.

937
01:10:30.430 --> 01:10:32.300
This is not nonfat.

938
01:10:32.640 --> 01:10:34.060
Oh.

939
01:10:34.220 --> 01:10:38.270
I love your books. Your shit's brilliant.

940
01:10:38.440 --> 01:10:40.020
Cathy?

941
01:10:41.020 --> 01:10:43.730
- You seem drunk.
- Little bit.

942
01:10:43.900 --> 01:10:45.730
Never made it to bed last night.

943
01:10:45.900 --> 01:10:48.280
But I type like a motherfucker!

944
01:10:48.450 --> 01:10:50.450
I have a degree in finance
from Princeton...

945
01:10:50.620 --> 01:10:53.280
...and I've been assistant to a V.P.
At Merrill Lynch.

946
01:10:53.450 --> 01:10:58.580
That's impressive. And, Paul'
why do you think you're right for this job?

947
01:11:06.380 --> 01:11:11.050
- So you're from St. Louis?
- That's right. Louise from St. Louis.

948
01:11:11.220 --> 01:11:13.140
And you have a degree
in computer science?

949
01:11:13.300 --> 01:11:16.310
- Yes, that's correct.
- Well, good for you. I can barely text.

950
01:11:18.350 --> 01:11:22.020
- Have you ever been a personal assistant?
- No, but I'm the oldest of six kids...

951
01:11:22.190 --> 01:11:24.400
...so I'm sure I can handle
anything you got.

952
01:11:24.570 --> 01:11:27.400
- Wow. Six kids, what's that like?
- Crowded.

953
01:11:27.860 --> 01:11:30.990
I had to move to New York just to
get some room. Where did I end up?

954
01:11:31.160 --> 01:11:33.780
In a one-bedroom apartment
with three roommates.

955
01:11:34.280 --> 01:11:37.450
Well, aside from the space issue'
why'd you move to New York?

956
01:11:39.370 --> 01:11:40.660
To fall in love.

957
01:11:42.210 --> 01:11:45.540
- What? That's corny, right?
- No.

958
01:11:45.710 --> 01:11:49.720
No, no, it's... It's just very honest.

959
01:11:50.720 --> 01:11:54.930
I don't think that I've heard
anybody say that in a very long time.

960
01:11:55.470 --> 01:11:56.810
Well...

961
01:11:58.730 --> 01:12:02.060
So Louise from St. Louis,
I just have one more question.

962
01:12:02.230 --> 01:12:03.270
Okay.

963
01:12:03.480 --> 01:12:05.810
How does an unemployed girl
with three roommates...

964
01:12:05.980 --> 01:12:08.530
...afford the Patchwork Denim Bowley
Louis Vuitton bag?

965
01:12:08.900 --> 01:12:13.280
It's rented. Bag Borrow or Steal?
It's like Netflix for purses.

966
01:12:13.450 --> 01:12:17.240
- How can I not know about this?
- Girl, stick with me. I'll hook you up.

967
01:12:22.250 --> 01:12:25.290
And did she hook me up.

968
01:12:25.840 --> 01:12:29.840
Hi. This is Louise.
I'm calling for Carrie Bradshaw.

969
01:12:30.470 --> 01:12:34.550
Yes, she received your invitation,
but she will be unable to attend.

970
01:12:34.720 --> 01:12:36.350
Thank you.

971
01:12:40.430 --> 01:12:42.480
Put that over there.

972
01:12:43.600 --> 01:12:45.440
After only three days...

973
01:12:45.610 --> 01:12:50.280
...I began to think of her
as Saint Louise from St. Louis.

